<TEXT>
floridas second sweep of drug users and dealers 
netted more than 1400 arrests by friday evening as authorities 
combined reverse sting and trojan horse operations with search 
warrants and highway surveillance 
i think the idea is to just get as much crack off the street as 
we can and to once again send a message to people that are buying 
and selling crack that its not going to be tolerated said jim 
liljedal spokesman for the broward county sheriffs office 
by 1100 pm friday the roundup produced 6683 crack cocaine 
rocks 26 pounds of cocaine powder 1044 pounds of marijuana 52 
firearms 209 vehicles and 54667 in cash 
a total of 1465 arrests had been made by friday evening in the 
operation staffed by an estimated 1200 officers in all of the 
states 67 counties 
the 48hour crackdown dubbed operation rock pile ii was 
launched at 1201 am thursday and was coordinated by the florida 
sheriffs association 
a total of 2076 arrests were made in the first operation rock 
pile begun june 31 it also netted 3510 crack cocaine rocks 10 
pounds of cocaine powder 3 pounds of marijuana 327 vehicles 50 
firearms and 55107 cash 
crack a derivative of cocaine is sold in small chunks called 
rocks 
the only thing that surprised us intially was what seemed to be 
an unsually high amount of marijuana liljedal said at the 
operations command post in fort lauderdale 
in reverse stings officers pose as drug sellers and bust 
customers 
in trojan horse operations several deputies ride hidden in the 
back of a truck and jump out to make arrests when the driver is 
offered crack for sale by street corner dealers 
nothing seems to deter these people when theyre looking for 
crack or looking to sell it said liljedal 
</TEXT>
