motivated solely by the three mens mindless homophobia said 
justice william newsom in the appeals courts 21 ruling 
the court cited the legal standard for murder when no intent to 
kill is shown acting deliberately and in disregard for human life 
a person must commit an act that is inherently lifethreatening 
that standard cannot be met by a beating unless it is so brutal 
that death is a probable consequence said newsom 
