deputy foreign minister benjamin netanyahu speaking on israel 
radio said israel was not asked to conduct an investigation either 
by colombia or by the united states but has offered its cooperation 
to both countries 
two days ago we asked the colombian government at the request 
of foreign minister moshe arens for any information available to 
them and we have offered them assistance with anything we can do 
netanyahu said 
on friday an israeli reserve officer denied reports he was 
involved in training death squads for colombian drug lords saying 
instead he was an instructor for a group of cattle breeders fighting 
leftist guerrillas 
israel television and all of the countrys major dailies last 
week identified lt col yair klein as the head of a group of four 
israeli army reserve colonels who allegedly helped train 
paramilitary troops and assassination teams in colombia 
klein 44 a retired commander of a paratroop antiterror unit 
and president of a private security firm called spearhead was 
identified in israel on the basis of film broadcast by nbc 
i trained a group of farmers who defended themselves against 
terrorist organizations mostly the group called m19 a guerrilla 
group with the goal of turning colombia into cuba or nicaragua 
klein told national television friday 
a senior defense ministry official said klein probably will be 
questioned about his activities in colombia klein returned to 
israel on friday from the united states the television said 
netanyahu has said israel may revoke the passports of any israeli 
mercenaries proven to be involved in the training of death squads 
for colombian drug lords 
israel he said had set up an interdepartmental committee to 
look into this in the foreign ministry and other offices of the 
government 
klein said four spearhead instructors started to train a group of 
cattle breeders 18 months ago he said the training lasted for six 
months and the film was a concluding film of the training 
this group included only farmers who have been physically 
injured by guerrilla bullets and survived or had their families 
killed nobody else was accepted into this organization he said 
klein said the organization enjoyed the tacit support of the 
colombian government the first meeting with the group was preceded 
by a meeting in bogota that included a deputy government minister 
two senior officers and a representative of a bank 
he said military equipment and ammunition was used during the 
training which was conducted in full view of an army camp 
the colombian government cannot say it did not know anything 
about our training of such a group i estimate it was interested in 
such bodies being trained to solve the guerrilla problem klein 
said 
he said he was convinced that the group spearhead trained was not 
involved in drugs but he left open the possibility that it was 
doing so secretly 
on thursday the israeli defense ministry said in an official 
statement that spearhead has been denied a permit and operated 
illegally in colombia 
it said a second firm which it did not identify had violated 
terms of a permit to do security work in colombia but that no link 
to illegal activities had been established 
klein responded that he did not have a permit to work with 
official bodies but didnt need one to work with private groups 
he said spearhead entered colombia with the help of an israeli 
company that provided security services for the banana plantation 
owners union he declined to identify the company 
klein said his firm ended contacts with the group when we felt 
we were not needed and had a feeling the government started to 
ignore the body we trained 
the israelis he said were replaced by two mercenaries from 
scotland one from the united states and one from south africa he 
said the organization may later have gotten involved in drugs 
i estimate there is no organization today in colombia that is 
not linked to drugs from the government downwards klein said 
