the cartel is the worlds largest cocainetrafficking organization 
and supplies an estimated 80 percent of the cocaine distributed in 
the united states 
dozens of luxurious homes apartments and offices believed owned 
by gacha were among hundreds of properties siezed in an 
eightdayold offensive by police and military forces nationwide 
the unprecendented crackdown was prompted by the assassination of 
a highly popular presidential candidate sen luis carlos galan 
police in bogota announced the arrest of eight more suspects in 
galans killing aug 16 at a political rally on bogotas southern 
outskirts bringing to 13 the total of suspected participants or 
accomplices under arrest 
five heavily armed men were arrested in a surprise raid last week 
at a downtown bogota apartment four of them were identified by more 
than a dozen witnesses at the rally 
galans killing capped a 48hour wave of assassinations 
including that of a national police colonel in medellin and a 
prominent bogota magistrate it outraged colombian society and 
inspired the government crackdown backed by a series of tough 
emergency decrees by president virgilio barco 
barco renewed extradition with the united states and streamlined 
the procedure to reduce the need for extensive judicial review 
under bloody intimidation by traffickers the supreme court 
nullified the extradition treaty in june 1987 
about 11000 people have been detained in the government sweep 
including a handful of suspects described by colombian authorities 
as major traffickers or drugmoney managers wanted by the united 
states 
drug and legal experts at the us embassy were working over the 
weekend to try to arrange the extradition of some of the suspects 
sources said as were colombian justice officials 
on friday authorities disclosed the arrest in medellin of 
rodriguez gachas alleged finance chief luis fernando galeano 
berrio army officials said he was wanted in the united states on 
drug charges 
they said they also arrested freddy rodriguez a son of rodriguez 
gacha and that he also is wanted in the united states but there 
was no immediate us confirmation american narcotics experts in 
bogota previously have confirmed that three other suspects arrested 
in the sweep are wanted by us courts 
cartel bosses such as rodriguez gacha pablo escobar and jorge 
ochoa continue to elude authorities 
according to the bogota daily el espectador rodriguez gacha 
escaped to brazil wednesday in a private aircraft local press 
reports have placed escobar the medellin cartels most notorious 
leader in panama 
the raids on drug estates have revealed a penchant for the 
luxurious the kinky and the macabre at one ranch owned by 
rodriguez gacha soldiers found a wooden gallows but said they have 
no idea if it was ever used 
another drug lords estate featured a twostory stone playhouse 
for children built like a medieval castle opulent mirrored 
bedrooms with tiger skins valuable paintings and other works of 
art saunas and indoor swimming pools are common features 
at a mansion outside bogota believed to belong to reputed 
trafficker camilo zapata the army uncovered a room filled with 
articles of withcraft including potions dried tigers feet 
rotting vegetables and fruit and images of christ immersed in 
alcohol 
