from scientists to policyshapers in both countries who need to 
take action redford said 
during the conference scientists predicted that the greenhouse 
effect caused by rising levels of atmospheric carbon dioxide and 
other gases produced by industrial societies could raise global 
temperatures by 2 to 10 degrees over the next century that could 
alter worldwide weather patterns and cause the melting of the polar 
ice caps flooding coastal regions 
to combat the rise of carbon dioxide much of which comes from 
the burning of fossil fuels the letter proposes the two superpowers 
form an environmental security alliance to 
promote energyefficient technology 
halt production and use by the year 2000 of chlorofluorocarbons 
another group of greenhouse gases and substantially reduce 
carbon dioxide and other greenhouse gases 
reduce the rate of worldwide deforestation and start the 
planting of trees in unforested areas 
the letter was accompanied by a conference report detailing 
specific strategies for reducing global warming 
in the past redfords institute for resource management a 
private environmental mediation group based at his sundance resort 
in central utah has tackled offshore drilling in the bering sea 
